	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, Jan 27th 9:35 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Okay, here's the deal.  I currently play a plethera of characters, but my main is a 23 Dwarven Cleric.  Now, as I have (As have many of you, I'm sure) experienced, in group combat involving several MoB's at a time, the second I cast a healing spell I get at least one of them on me.  =(  This has, in one instance cost me my life (Nearly my precious 23rd level) and the life of a group mate.  My question is this;<br>I am aware of the need for AC and even possibly dex (Or is it agi?  Well, whichever one helps in your ability to dodge and be missed in melee).  I'm not sure if my Wis is appropriate for my level (133 or so), but my mana seems plentiful enough as long as my tanks don't get drunk and think they're invincible Gods, which has on occasion happened.  But I'm hoping to find a balance between Wis stats and defensive stats.  Any ideas on how I can accomplish this?  Particular items I may be able to aquire at my level?  Numeric goals for various stats, perhaps?  Any feedback and advice would be greatly appreciated, as I don't want to continue becoming more of a liability to a group, rather than an asset.  I would prefer the ability to dodge an attack or two while my tanks try to taunt the MoB off of me, or while I try to root it so that I can get back to my primary function of keeping everyone else alive and not worrying about my own little red bar.  =)<br>Anyway, thank you for reading, and have fun.  Remember;<br><br>It's only a game!<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
